CommonFields.Title: Synthesis and properties of fluorine-containing polybenzimidazole/silica nanocomposite membranes for proton exchange membrane fuel cells
Author: Chuang, Shih-Wei
Hsu, Steve Lien-Chung
Liu, Yen-Hsin
CommonFields.Location: Department of Materials Science and Engineering, Frontier Material and Micro/Nano Science and Technology Center, National Cheng-Kung University, 1 Ta-Hsueh Road, Tainan 70101, Taiwan, ROC

Mixing.Description: 3,3 -diaminobenzidine was dissolved in 12.9067 g of poly(phosphoric acid) (PPA) in a 250-mL, three-necked, round-bottom flask equipped with a mechanical stirrer and a condenser.
Mixture was stirred until it became homogeneous.

ChooseParameter.Other: 0.3432 g (0.875 mmol) of 2,2-bis(4- carboxyphenyl)hexafluoropropane and 0.0683 g (0.375 mmol) of 5-hydroxyisophthalic acid were added
The mixture reacted at 200 ◦C for 24 h
The PPA with P2O5 content at 84.5% was diluted with 85% phosphoric acid and water.

Mixing.Description: Mixture was stirred overnight to hydrolyze the phosphate ester.
Resultant was added dropwise to 1 L of deionized water

ChooseParameter.Other: The precipitated polymer was collected by filtration and washed with deionized water several times.

Mixing.Description: PBI30OH powder was dissolved in DMAc

ChooseParameter.Other: (3-isocyanatopropyl)triethoxysilane was added to the solution as a bonding agent

Mixing.Description: A catalytic amount of triethylamine was added and the mixture was stirred at rt with a nitrogen inlet.

ChooseParameter.Other: tetraethoxysilane (TEOS) and deionized water was added to the solution

Mixing.Description: A catalytic amount of diethylamine was added and the mixture was stirred at rt.

MoldingInfo.Description: The solution was cast onto a glass plate with a doctor's knife.

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Dried in vacuum oven at rt

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: equipped with an energy dispersive X-ray (EDX) spectrometer

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Equipment: TA Instrument Thermal Mechanical Analyzer (TMA) Q400EM
